BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 52 486 Tm (8. How the System Works) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 461 Tm (1. The user opens the Flask application in the browser.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 446 Tm (2. Public routes call repository.py to request data from SQL Server.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 431 Tm (3. SQL results are returned to Flask as dictionaries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 416 Tm (4. Jinja templates render the data into public pages.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 401 Tm (5. Public forms submit data back to Flask.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 386 Tm (6. Flask validates the form input.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 371 Tm (7. Valid records are inserted into SQL Server.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 356 Tm (8. Administrator users sign in through the SQL-backed login route.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 341 Tm (9. The admin dashboard reads, updates, and manages the same database records.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 326 Tm (10. Important admin actions are logged in the audit table.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 52 303 Tm (9. Deployment / Running Steps) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 278 Tm (1. Open the project in VS Code.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 263 Tm (2. Ensure the Python virtual environment is selected.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 248 Tm (3. Run the SQL script in SSMS 22:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 233 Tm (- database/CreateKenyaEnvironmentPortal.sql) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 218 Tm (4. Check the SQL Server connection string in config.py.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 203 Tm (5. Start the app:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 188 Tm (- .\\.venv\\Scripts\\python.exe app.py) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 173 Tm (6. Open the public portal:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 158 Tm (- http://127.0.0.1:5000) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 143 Tm (7. Open the admin portal:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 58 128 Tm (- http://127.0.0.1:5000/admin/login) Tj ET
